Synopsis:
Yash Raj Films’ Saiyaara is an intense love story, that launches Ahaan Panday and Aneet Padda as the next YRF hero and heroine respectively. 

Directed by Mohit Suri, a master of the romance genre, Saiyaara tells a pure-hearted love story of two youngsters Vaani and Krish. While Vaani writes, Krish sings and they both make music together. Though poles apart in their lives, beliefs and backgrounds, Vaani and Krish are perfect with each other and for each other. Will they understand that truth despite their age, their problems? 

They say flawed, imperfect people make for a perfect love story…and Saiyaara is about celebrating that one love story that is so deep, so pure and so caring that it is absolutely unconditional.

Vaani and Krish will have to navigate life, their problems, their insecurities to hopefully realise that only love can be the answer to everything. Saiyaara is a film that celebrates every season of love through the eyes of Vaani & Krish and poses a simple question…do you love someone so much that you would bet everything to keep that person in your life?

snippet.title: Thangapoovey - Video Song | Madharaasi | Sivakarthikeyan | Rukmini | A.R.Murugadoss | Anirudh
snippet.description:
Junglee Music Tamil presents the video song of “Thangapoovey” from the much-awaited film Madharaasi, written and directed by acclaimed filmmaker A.R. Murugadoss. Featuring the charismatic Sivakarthikeyan and the graceful Rukmini Vasanth in lead roles, this soulful track is composed by none other than Anirudh Ravichander, known for his chart-topping melodies and heart-touching compositions. Thangapoovey blends emotion with melody, capturing the essence of love and longing with poetic visuals and heartfelt lyrics.

With its mesmerizing tune and lyrical depth, Thangapoovey promises to strike a chord with music lovers and fans of Tamil cinema alike. Whether you're a follower of romantic Tamil songs or a die-hard fan of Anirudh’s music, this lyrical video is a must-watch. As anticipation builds for Madharaasi, this song sets the perfect tone, offering a glimpse into the film’s emotional landscape.

snippet.title: The Chase teaser, #Madhavan and #Dhoni stepping into character as officers on a high-stakes mission
snippet.description:
MS Dhoni has done just about everything on a cricket field, masterminded chases, stayed cool under fire, and even walked away with three ICC trophies. But now, the former India skipper has turned heads for something very different: wielding guns in an action-packed teaser alongside Bollywood star R Madhavan.

What came as a big surprise on August 7, Madhavan surprised fans by dropping the clip of his upcoming project The Chase, directed by Vasan Bala. The teaser shows both Madhavan and Dhoni dressed in tactical black gear, complete with bulletproof vests and sunglasses, stepping into character as officers on a high-stakes mission. The sight of “Captain Cool” in an action sequence sent social media into overdrive, with fans already dubbing it Dhoni’s big-screen debut.

snippet.title: Alcohol - Official Teaser | Allari Naresh, Ruhani Sharma, Niharika Nm  | Meher Tej | S Naga Vamsi
snippet.description:
Watch Alcohol - Official Teaser | Allari Naresh, Ruhani Sharma, Niharika Nm  | Meher Tej | S Naga Vamsi 

Alcohol is a Telugu feature film starring Allari Naresh, Ruhani Sharma, Niharika NM, Satya, and an ensemble cast. Directed by Meher Tej, the film features music by Ghibran, background score by Chaitan Bharadwaj, cinematography by Jiju Sunny, and editing by Niranjan Devaramane.

Produced by Suryadevara Naga Vamsi and Sai Soujanya under Sithara Entertainments and Fortune Four Cinemas, the film is presented by Srikara Studios.

Cast: Allari Naresh, Ruhani Sharma, Niharika NM, Satya, Girish Kulkarni, Harshavardhan, Chaitanya Krishna, Ravindra Vijay, Raghu Babu, Venkatesh Kakumanu, Kireeti, Hariteja, Surya Bhagavan Das, Flora Jacob

Crew:
Written & Directed by – Meher Tej
Producers – S. Naga Vamsi, Sai Soujanya
Co-Producer – Venkat Upputuri
Music – Ghibran
Background Score – Chaitan Bharadwaj
DOP – Jiju Sunny
Production Designer – Vishal Abani
Editor – Niranjan Devaramane
Teaser Cut – Niranjan Devaramane
Co-Writer – Udbhav Raghunandan
Art Director – Dinesh Kumar
Sound Mixing – Mr. Rajakrishnan
Sound Designer – Saumit Sunil Deshmukh
DI – Shanmugha Pandian
VFX Supervisor – Ramji Dott

Alcohol hits theatres worldwide on January 1st, 2026 – a perfect New Year festive release!

Alcohol is a Telugu feature film starring Allari Naresh, Ruhani Sharma, Niharika NM, Satya, and an ensemble cast. Directed by Meher Tej, the film features music by Ghibran, background score by Chaitan Bharadwaj, cinematography by Jiju Sunny, and editing by Niranjan Devaramane.

हमसे काहे बड़ियारी खेसारी कइल
तुहु लागता की पंकज बिहारी भईल
आशु प्रियांशु मालिश क देल
ताकत से ज्यादा हिरिष क देल
हई किस लेके ओठ किशमिश 
कमर 28 से 30 क देल, हई किस लेके.....

Naam yeh mera 
ik dafa toh le 
Haazir ho jaunga 
main teri khidmat mein 
Teri haan ya naa sab qubool 

Zindagi se main
maangoon mannatein 
Meri saansien bahein 
teri hi qurbat mein 
Tere sang main rahoon ba-usool 

Teri yeh narm dhoop se 
hain chaar chaand lag gaye 
din pe 

Tu woh mehak alaav ki 
jo door se bhi sekti 
mera dil yeh 

Kaafi hai bas Tera Hona 
par chaahoon main tera hona 
Koi ho ya ho na 
tum toh ho na

Antra:
Tu woh kitaab hai jisey 
saari umar sambhaal ke 
rakhna maine (rakhna maine)
Mila hoon jab se main tujhe 
bhoola woh zindagi jo thi 
bin tere 

Tera hi zikr goonjta 
meri yeh dhadkanon ki 
vaadi mein 

Tu woh mehak alaav ki 
jo door se bhi sekti 
mera dil yeh 

Kaafi hai bas Tera Hona 
par chaahoon main tera hona 
Koi ho ya ho na 
tum toh ho na

snippet.title: Ram Jaane (Music Video) Anu Malik | Shahrukh Khan, Juhi Chawla | Alka Yagnik, Sonu Nigam|Hindi song
snippet.description:
“Ram Jaane” is the bold and unforgettable title track from the 1995 Bollywood action-drama Ram Jaane, sung by Udit Narayan, Alka Yagnik, Sonu Nigam and composed by Anu Malik. The song captures the gritty, rebellious spirit of the film’s lead character, played by Shah Rukh Khan, whose very name — Ram Jaane (meaning “God knows”) — becomes a powerful identity statement.

#RamJaane #ShahRukhKhan #JuhiChawla #UditNarayan #AlkaYagnik #SonuNigam #AnuMalik #BollywoodClassics #SRKMovies #BollywoodAction #HindiMovieSongs #RamJaaneSong #BollywoodHits #EvergreenBollywood #SRKFans #BollywoodSoundtrack #ClassicSRK #IndianCinema #BollywoodAnthems #BollywoodThrowback #DesiVibes 

Credits: 
Singer: Udit Narayan, Alka Yagnik, Sonu Nigam
Music: Anu Malik
Lyrics: Anand Bakshi
Movie: Ram Jaane
Starring: Shahrukh Khan, Juhi Chawla
Director: Rajiv Mehra
Producer: Parvesh Mehra
Label: Universal Music India

Lyrics:

Kehthe hain log muje "ram jaane"
Kaise padaa ye mera naam jaane
Kaise padaa ye mera naam jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
O, ram jaane, ye to bataa
Tere sa dil ka raaja bana
Paise ka kaise ghulaam jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
♪
Yaaron, mazaa lene do zaraa sa
Barson raha hoon main bhookha-pyaasaa
Vo ik haqiqat hai, o, deewaane
Samajh hai tune jiskoo tamaasha
♪
Mat chhed mujko, aa hosh mein
Paagal javanee ke josh mein
Mat chhed mujko, aa hosh mein
Paagal javanee ke josh mein
Too pee gaya kithne jam jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
♪
Jo jhooth-sach ko pahachaanata hai
Duniyaa mein jeenaa vo jaanata hai
Hum kya karen, hum tujhse alag hain
Hum maut ko zindagi maanata hai
♪
Maranaa hai ik din saba ko, magar
O, bekhabar, tujko kya khabar
Maranaa hai ik din saba ko, magar
O, bekhabar, tujko kya khabar
Kya hai tera anjaam jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
♪
Kaise tera toota dil jod doon main?
Dil chaahe saba ka dil tod doon main
Ho, nafrat naa kar, khud se pyaar kar too
Too "haan " kahe to ye zid chhod doon main
♪
Ye to naseebon ka kaam hai
Har dil pe likhaa ek naam hai
Ye to naseebon ka kaam hai
Har dil pe likhaa ek naam hai
Kis pe likhaa kis ka naam jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Kehthe hain log muje "ram jaane"
Kaise padaa ye mera naam jaane
Kaise padaa ye mera naam jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane
Ram jaane, ram jaane

snippet.description:
🙏 Monday Special – Lord Shiva Devotional Songs 🙏

Start your week with the blessings of Lord Shiva by listening to these powerful Telugu devotional songs. Mondays are considered especially auspicious for worshipping Lord Shiva, and chanting or listening to his songs is believed to bring peace, prosperity, and spiritual strength.

In this video, you can enjoy Shivuni Patalu (Lord Shiva Songs in Telugu) curated for Monday worship. Immerse yourself in devotion, feel the divine presence, and seek the blessings of Lord Shiva for a happy and prosperous life.

✨ Perfect for daily prayers, meditation, and spiritual upliftment.
✨ Share the devotion with friends and family to spread positivity.
✨ Let the powerful chants of Lord Shiva remove obstacles and negativity.

🙏 If you liked this video, please Like 👍, Share 🔄, and Subscribe 🔔 to our channel for more devotional songs and spiritual content.

#MondaySongs #ShivuniPatalu #LordShivaSongs #telugudevotionalsongs #telugubhaktisongs

As the lyrics unfold, we witness the infinite depth of his affection—how each night is never complete without her warm goodnight wishes, and no morning dawns without her sweet greeting, creating a rhythm of love that enfolds their everyday existence.

snippet.title: Chitthi Aayi Hai | Pankaj Udhas | Laxmikant-Pyarelal | Anand Bakshi | Old Hindi Song
snippet.description:
Relive the golden era of Bollywood with the soulful classic “Chitthi Aayi Hai” sung by the legendary Pankaj Udhas. This evergreen melody, composed by the iconic duo Laxmikant–Pyarelal and penned by the great lyricist Anand Bakshi, beautifully captures emotions of love, separation, and longing.

👉 A timeless gem from the treasure of Old Hindi Songs, this track continues to touch millions of hearts even today.
Perfect for lovers of 90s Bollywood songs, ghazals, and evergreen melodies.

Don’t forget to like, share for more musical journeys through Bollywood’s golden era.

Film:  Naam
Song: Chitthi Aai Hai
Artist: Pankaj Udhas
Music Director: Laxmikant Pyarelal
Lyricist: Anand Bakshi
Filmstar: Kumar Gaurav/Poonam Dhillon/Sanjay Dutt/Amrita Singh/Nutan/Anupam Kher/Pankaj Udhas
Director: Mahesh Bhatt

पौराणिक ग्रंथो में भाद्रपद पूर्णिमा की एक कथा काफी प्रचलित है। द्वापर युग में एक बार यशोदा मां ने भगवान श्री कृष्ण से पूछा कि वह उन्हें एक ऐसा व्रत बताएं जिसको करने से मृत्यु लोक में स्त्रियों को विधवा होने का भय ना रहे तथा वह व्रत मनुष्यों की सभी मनोकामनाएं पूर्ण करने वाला हो।
